name: ParseHtml

values.name: document
values.comment:
Parser for an HTML document. Requires a DOCTYPE declaration and at least one HTML element to succeed. Parser.run document "" == Ok (Element "html" [] []) Parser.run document "

I am a document!

" = Element "html" [] [ Element "head" [] [], Element "body" [] [ Element "h1" [] [ TextNode "I am a document!" ]] ]

values.name: parseDocument
values.comment:
Runs the document parser.

    parseDocument "<!DOCTYPE html><html></html>" == Ok (Element "html" [] [])

name: ParseHtml.Node.Element

values.name: element
values.comment:
Parses an HTML element. Parser.run element "

" == Ok (Element "p" [] []) Parser.run element "

" == Ok (Element "p" [("class", "myclass")] []) Parser.run element "

Hi!

" == Ok (Element "p" [] [ TextNode "Hi!" ])

name: ParseHtml.Node.Comment

values.name: comment
values.comment:
Parses an HTML comment

    Parser.run comment "<!--Comment!-->" == Ok (Comment "Comment!")

name: ParseHtml.Node.Text

values.name: textNode
values.comment:
Parses an HTML text node (this will succeed on any string not starting with a "<" character, so make sure you run other parsers first).

    Parser.run textNode "some text" == Ok (textNode "some text")
    Parser.run textNode "<some text" == Err BadRepeat

name: ParseHtml.Node.Model

types.name: Node
types.comment:
Represents an HTML node. In most common use, will probably represent a complete tree of HTML elements parsed from an HTML document.

    rootNode = Element "html" [] [ Element "head" [] [], Element "body" [] [ Element "h1" [] [ TextNode "I am a document!" ]] ]
